Hi David
Usually this is from a Back fire pop,,, and /. or a loose rubber boot,,,
replace your rubber boot, and check you vac level with a gauge. The gauge
should be above 15hg at idle and steady.  If it is fluctuating,, adjust your
valves, and check the vac level again.

Hope that helps
